description:
&lt;p&gt;This is a fantastic prospect for the right person to further develop their skills in stroke rehabilitation from acute to rehab/recovery. Working alongside specialist and dedicated clinicians to provide high quality integrated care for patients through seamless Multidisciplinary and Multi-agency working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post would be suited to an existing Band 5 looking to further develop and consolidate their expertise in stroke rehabilitation with a desire to develop within an outstanding service. This is an exciting post that will offer great stretch and opportunity for the right person.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our therapy team is a dedicated team, and you will need to be enthusiastic, highly motivated and be able to demonstrate excellent communication and organisational skills and an ability to work as part of a multi-disciplinary working team that are truly person centered in their approach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post in return offers excellent opportunities to develop your clinical and personal skills within a friendly environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have a BSc in Occupational Therapy or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be HCPC Registered&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have significant NHS experince&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recent experience in rehabilitation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Well-developed clinical reasoning skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evidence of CPD and self-directed post graduate learning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of Multidisciplinary working in a variety of settings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fran Platts Job title Therapy operational Manager Email address fran.platts@nhs.net Telephone number 01623785177&lt;/p&gt;
